data.name: label1.Text
data.value: Pig is a simple one-player dice game were a player tries to accumulate as many points as possible. The game consists of five turns. The final score is the sum of the scores from each turn. During each turn, the player repeatedly rolls the die until either a 1 is rolled or the player decides not to roll any more for that turn. • If a one is rolled, the player gets zero points for the turn and the turn immediately ends. • If any other number is rolled, it is added to the total for that turn and the player has the option to roll again, if they wish.
